   DORCHESTER COLLECTION

Le Meurice

   The original palace hotel in the heart of historic Paris, Le Meurice
   with its splendid newly-restored rooms and suites is the very epitome
   of quiet elegance and is alive with the artist’s soul of wit and magic.

   Location:
   Le Meurice,
   228 rue de Rivoli, 75001 Paris
   Call:
   +33 (0) 1 44 58 10 10

It’s time to take another look at the hotel of artists and thinkers, in the
heart of Paris, as we unveil 29 newly-restored rooms and suites inspired by
the beauty of Versailles.

   Contact
     * Culture
     * Restored rooms & suites
     * Experience
     * Gifts & Experiences

   Contact
     * Culture
     * Restored rooms & suites
     * Experience
     * Gifts & Experiences

   CULTURE

A living work of art

   Le Meurice is an inspirational and fascinating place where 18th-century
   splendour and the most innovative modern comforts sit happily side by
   side. So much more than a luxury hotel, this is a gallery, an
   adventure, a living work of art.

   Discover more

   History

The story of Paris in a hotel

   Like the city itself, Le Meurice has been shaped by the artists who
   have called it home. From Dalí and Zola to Warhol and Dylan, the hotel
   has provided repose and inspiration for the many iconic characters who
   have added fresh layers of richness to our history with every passing
   year.

   Discover more
   History - The story of Paris in a hotel
   History - The story of Paris in a hotel detail

   Your stay

Wake up in the heart of the city – where history and the contemporary combine
with spirited panache. Here you have the Tuileries Garden as your front
garden, the Louvre to your left and Place de la Concorde to your right. Paris
is yours.

   ROOMS & SUITES

A modern-day Versailles

   Discover our selection of newly-restored rooms and suites, overlooking
   all the major city landmarks, marking a new chapter in our illustrious
   history.
   Explore
   Views

Understand Paris from within

   The city waits to be seen. Choose to gaze at the leafy splendour of the
   Tuileries Garden, the finest monuments of Paris, the lively beauty of
   traditional streets or typical Parisian courtyards where the tranquil
   rituals of daily life play out.
   Unique

Where time becomes art

   Mirroring the surrealism of Dalí himself, Le Meurice is removed from
   the rigours of time. This is a hotel that blends traditional splendour
   and modern luxury with a personality rooted in the artistic flair of
   Parisian history.
   Location

The heart of historical Paris

   Only 15 minutes from the Eurostar and 30 minutes from the airport, just
   steps away from the Louvre museum and luxury shopping. Everything you
   could want to know of Paris is within walking distance of Le Meurice.

   True luxury is invisible. At Le Meurice, you find it in the elegance,
   harmony and prestige of the hotel and in the flawless service provided
   by our devoted staff.

   Franka Holtmann General Manager, Le Meurice

   Experience

A story begun by royalty and designed by our greatest artists, now ready for
you to write your own chapter.

Gilded glory, glittering history

   An awe-inspiring room full of golden light and shimmering memories. The
   sparkling nineteenth century décor of this stunning stateroom evokes
   the grandeur of Versailles and the rich heritage of this elegant hotel.
   Explore

An afternoon tea adventure like no other

   Cédric Grolet, our celebrated pastry chef, is the undisputed master of
   his art. Afternoon tea is reinterpreted with his dazzling passion,
   becoming deliciously unforgettable.
   Explore

Your wedding in the city of romance

   An elegant address, a beautiful space. All seamlessly choreographed by
   our skilled team. We deliver wonderful days.
   Explore
   SPA

Serenity for the body, mind and soul

   The only Valmont spa in Paris, where nature and science blend to
   achieve powerful results. This exclusive sanctum brings peace with
   style, all washed in the signature Valmont green.
   Explore

   GIFTS & EXPERIENCES
   Pull out all the stops
